##                                                   ##
## The silicon carbide evaluation improved the       ##
## ENDF/B-VIII.0 evaluation with key improvements    ##
## listed below:                                     ##
## - Mass and free atom cross sections were updated  ##
##   to use ENDF/B-VIII.0 values with natural        ##
##   abundances taken from NIST.                     ##
## - Lattice constants used to evaluate the coherent ## 
##   elastic were updated to experimental values [5].##
## - The DOS was improved with additional resolution ##
##   to capture more resolution.                     ##
## - The coherent elastic evaluation was improved    ##
##   with use of the current FLASSH 1.0 algorithms.  ##
##                                                   ##
##                                                   ##
##                                                   ## 
##   1. A.I. Hawari, "Modern Techniques in Inelastic ## 
##      Thermal Neutron Scattering Analysis," Nucl.  ##
##      Data Sheets 118, 172 (2014).                 ##
##                                                   ##
##   2. N.C. Fleming, et al., "FLASSH 1.0: Thermal   ##
##      Scattering Law Evaluation and Cross Section  ##
##      Generation for Reactor Physics               ##
##      Applications," Nucl. Sci. and Eng. (2023).   ##
##                                                   ##
##   3. D.A. Brown et. al., "ENDF/B-VIII.0: The 8th  ##
##      Major Release of the Nuclear Reaction Data   ##
##      Library with CIELO-project Cross Sections,   ##
##      New Standards and Thermal Scattering Data,"  ##
##      Nucl. Data Sheets, 148 (2018).               ##
##                                                   ##
##   4. M. Berglund and M.E. Wieser, "Isotpic        ##
##      Compositions of the Elements 2009 (IUPAC     ##
##      Technical Report)," Pure Appl. Chem, 83      ##
##      (2011).                                      ##
##                                                   ##
##   5. T. Kimoto and J.A. Cooper, Fundamentals of   ##
##      Silicon Carbide Technology: Growth,          ##
##      Characterization, Devices, and Applications, ##
